description.text:
Opera Sweden is looking for a DevOps Developer with a passion for technology and learning to join our diverse fin-tech team in Gothenburg where you get to build great products together with the team. Experimenting with new technology is in our DNA and our collaborative team is constantly trying to find better ways to build quality products. In our current project we have chosen to go with a TypeScript, React Native, React.js, Redux stack and invested in CI/CD and test automation using the popular Jest, Detox and Selenium frameworks. Product quality and iteration speed are crucial to building successful products and we believe writing tests should be a natural part of the development process. In this role you will be working in a supportive team of about 10 people with an agile workflow. Together with the rest of the team you will be part of design reviews, sprint planning, weekly sprints, continuous integration and delivery processes. The team is currently located in Gothenburg in a cozy office in the city center.
Role & Responsibilities:
Support the team by building and improving CI and CD;
Build monitoring and reporting for the project;
Set up the framework for incident management and recovery;
Cooperate with the development team to build the SDLC framework for the project;
Create a release plan with the management team and developers;
Manage allocation of cloud resources;
Establishing and advocating DevOps best practices in the team.

Job Requirements:
BS or MS in Computer Science or equivalent experience;
At least 2 years of recent employment in a DevOps role in the enterprise environment;
Experience with deployment and delivery of web apps, ability to build the infrastructure from scratch;
Familiarity with mainstream CI/CD for web apps: Docker, Jenkins, Kubernetes, Puppet;
Work experience with cloud hosting providers such as AWS;
Experience with load balancing and CDN, administration of Linux systems;

An Ideal Candidate’s Profile:
Been familiar with front-end tools: Babel, Webpack, NPM, linters, etc.;
Been familiar with monitoring tools such as Graphana, Loki, infrastructure-as-code tools such as Terraform;
Close-to-expert knowledge of git, experience with python, shell scripting and high availability systems;
The role requires fluency in English
Currently living in Gothenburg or willing to relocate;

Diversity and Inclusion
At Opera diversity and inclusion are central to our values. We recognise that being diverse and inclusive makes us stronger as a business. Our aim is to attract, recruit and retain people who reflect the diverse nature of our business, clients and communities regardless of nationality, ethnicity, faith, belief, sexual orientation, gender identity, social background, age and disability.
What’s on Offer:
An opportunity to connect with colleagues from all over the world
A flat organization structure and friendly atmosphere where we learn and grow together
A flexible work environment
Great company benefits

About Us:
Opera is a global web innovator with an engaged and growing base of hundreds of millions of monthly active users who seek a better internet experience. Building on over 25 years of innovation that started with browser products, Opera is now leveraging its brand and highly engaged user base in order to expand its business into new segments. Today, Opera offers users around the world a range of products and services that include PC and mobile browsers, the newsreader Opera News, and apps committed to gaming, e-commerce and classifieds.
Opera is headquartered in Oslo, Norway with major offices in Poland, China, Spain and Sweden, as well as a presence in many additional countries. Opera is listed on the Nasdaq stock exchange under the “OPRA” ticker symbol.
